'''人造皮膚'''是利用[[科技|科技]]，人為地製造皮膚以供[[皮膚|皮膚]]有問題如[[燒傷|燒傷]]的[[病人|病人]]替換。

==前言==
皮膚是人體最大的[[器官|器官]]，其用途是防止人體內的[[水分|水分]]散失和[[細菌|細菌]]感染。所以每當皮膚大面積被火燒燬，病人就會有[[脫水|脫水]]和細菌感染而引致[[死亡|死亡]]的危險。傳統處理燒傷有兩種方法。第一，從病人身上其他地方切取一部份的皮放在傷口上；第二，從其他人或[[生物|生物]]，如[[豬|豬]]的身上切取皮膚來代替。前者無法大量取得[[皮膚|皮膚]]，否則會在身體其他地方引發細菌感染。而後者雖然可以大量生產，但卻會引起[[排斥|排斥]]，從而導致死亡。為了解決以上問題，人造皮的技術誕生了<ref>Scientists Develop Artificial Skin|http://thefutureofthings.com/news/7236/scientists-develop-artificial-skin.html {{Wayback|url=http://thefutureofthings.com/news/7236/scientists-develop-artificial-skin.html |date=20111002101648 }}</ref>。

==生物人造皮==
目前製造人造皮有兩種方法。

第一種是先從病人身上提取[[膠原蛋白|膠原蛋白]]<ref>{{cite news|title=A Better Artificial Skin|url=http://www.technologyreview.com/biotech/18059/|work=[[Technology_Review|Technology Review]]|date=January 12, 2007|first=Emily|last=Singer|accessdate=February 15, 2010|archive-date=2012-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512145447/http://www.technologyreview.com/Biotech/18059/}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|title=Artificial Skin Developed at MIT Now Ready for Treatment with Burn Patients|url=http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/1996/artificialskin.html|publisher=[[MIT|MIT]]|date=April 12, 1996|accessdate=February 15, 2010|archive-date=2013-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130709184353/http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/1996/artificialskin.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft|date=January 4, 2008|title=Growing Artificial Skin From Hair Roots|work=[[Science_Daily|Science Daily]]|accessdate=February 15, 2010|url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/01/080104140344.htm|authorlink=Fraunhofer Society|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109031244/http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/01/080104140344.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，然後放在培養皿上培養成一塊皮膚。第二種則是從病人身上提取皮膚細胞<ref name="#1">Biotechnology Australia|Spray on Skin|{{cite web |url=http://www.biotechnology-innovation.com.au/innovations/pharmaceuticals/spray_on_skin.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2009-02-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227022803/http://www.biotechnology-innovation.com.au/innovations/pharmaceuticals/spray_on_skin.html |archivedate=2009-02-27 }}</ref>，只培養一堆細胞，然後把細胞噴在傷口上，讓其生長成皮膚。前者的缺點是平均要等待21<ref name="#1"/>天才培養出皮膚。後者雖然可以快速在病人身上生成皮膚，但仍然在實驗階段。

==非生物人造皮==
顧名思義，這種人造皮不是由[[細胞|細胞]]組成，而是用[[半導體|半導體]]<ref>Synthetic Skin Sensitive to the Lightest Touch|http://spectrum.ieee.org/biomedical/bionics/synthetic-skin-sensitive-to-the-lightest-touch {{Wayback|url=http://spectrum.ieee.org/biomedical/bionics/synthetic-skin-sensitive-to-the-lightest-touch |date=20191130022027 }}</ref>。當接觸物件時，半導體會產生[[電流|電流]]從而產生[[觸覺|觸覺]]。目前這種半導體人造皮用於[[機械人|機械人]]身上，為機械人提供觸覺。但科學家正在研究進一步應用在[[義肢|義肢]]上，讓失去肢體的人可以再次獲得觸覺。

